description:
First off, thank you all so much for this crazy opportunity and I just want to say regardless of how you may feel about all this, I considerate it a blessing and am so very grateful for it.

So this is a quick recap for those who couldn't watch the entire video for whatever reason (I know it's a long video, hahah):

1. I am leaving my university for 1 year to do YouTube full-time
2. I will now be uploading every single day at 1:30pm and 3:30pm EST (if I am unable to upload, I will let you all know).
3. If at the end of the year (May 1st, 2016) I have not reached 150,000 subscribers, or feel YouTube isn't a viable living source, I will need to leave YouTube to finish my degree.
4. It was a very tough decision and was thoroughly thought out and I have taken care of all the administrative business to begin this journey.
5. Moving out of my dorm May 1st, 2015 to begin.
6. I DO NOT make a lot of money from YouTube so it will be hard at times I already know.
7. I appreciate the support of all those close to me personally and of course you all. It really means more than the world to me.

So yeah, that's about it. Let's do this, together.

chapters.title: If YouTube doesn't work out, I'm stepping away...
